Discovery Cohort WGCNA Analysis

Data QC

## here() starts at /gfs/devel/majackson/BRC_WGCNA/Clean_Repo/Bulk_RNA_Analyses
## Allowing multi-threading with up to 20 threads.

Genes

TPM expression data loaded contains 99 samples and 57885 genes. This was filtered to only retain genes observed in at least 50% of samples, resulting in 22201 genes. TPM counts were then log transformed (log(x+1)) for further analyses.

Samples

Removed samples flagged for omission after failing QC in DE analysis, data now contains 82 samples. Heirarchical clustering plot to check for outliers and metadata associations.

No obvious outliers, reasonable clustering of control and IBD samples.

WGCNA

Define co-expression modules

Find a soft-threshold power to define a network between the genes. Using signed weights to define the network.

Use a soft-thresholding power of 9 to generate an adjaceny matrix of the network this threshold produces. Then generate a topological overlap matrix from the adjacency matrix using a block-wise approach.

Look at correlations between the module eigengenes.

After filtering a total of 22201 genes were included in module identification. These were clustered into modules by splitting data into 1 blocks. A total of 38 modules were identified (plus an additional unassigned module (grey)).

Module correlations with metadata

Find correlation between module eigengenes and metadata traits. Find modules associated with inflammation.

Modules/traits with at least one FDR significant correlation (FDR p<0.05)

## Scale for 'fill' is already present. Adding another scale for 'fill', which
## will replace the existing scale.
## Scale for 'colour' is already present. Adding another scale for 'colour',
## which will replace the existing scale.

It is clear that the modules are largely correlating with differences in inflammation status. Especially given the FDR adjusted p-values. Nicely, the medication traits are showing opposing effects. The only traits with no nominally significant module associations were immunosuppression. The only modules with no significant associations were M35, M36.

Summary of output files

discovery_module_analysis.html - This report showing all the steps in the analysis.

discovery_WGCNAgeneInfo.csv - Table showing the module assignment for each gene, its correlation with inflammation, and its correlation with all other modules.

discovery_WGCNAmodInfo.csv - Table showing the module correlations with all clinical traits including inflammation.

discovery_WGCNAGOEnrcihmentTable.csv - Table contianing the top 10 GO terms enriched for in each module.

TOM-block.-.Rds - Topological overlap matrices used to generate the modules (generated blockwise).

discovery_filtered_tpm.Rds - The TPMs after filtering used to make the modules. Passed to the network script to name the genes.

discovery_NANCY_module_correlations.tsv - Eigengene correlation values and significance for each module vs NANCY scores.

Additional plots not included in the markdown are network plots of the gene networks within each module, which are in Plots/Networks at various TOM thresholds.
